usdLogMIB.name: usdLogMIB

revisions.description: Replace single syslog destination with table of syslog destinations, and add syslog facility as an attribute for syslogs.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdLogMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdLogMIB.description: The Log MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

UsdLogCatName.name: UsdLogCatName
UsdLogCatName.description: The name of a log category. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
UsdLogCatName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

UsdLogVerbosity.name: UsdLogVerbosity
UsdLogVerbosity.description: The log verbosity level. Not all event types offer medium- or high-verbosity levels of detail.

usdLogDestSyslogSeverity.name: usdLogDestSyslogSeverity
usdLogDestSyslogSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the SYSLOG server. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are sent to this destination.

usdLogDestSyslogAddress.name: usdLogDestSyslogAddress
usdLogDestSyslogAddress.description: The IP address of the SYSLOG server to which log messages are to be sent. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates no server address is configured.

usdLogSyslogTable.name: usdLogSyslogTable
usdLogSyslogTable.description: A table describing the characteristics of each syslog destination.

usdLogSyslogEntry.name: usdLogSyslogEntry
usdLogSyslogEntry.description: An entry describingthe characteristics of a syslog destination.

usdLogSyslogIpAddress.name: usdLogSyslogIpAddress
usdLogSyslogIpAddress.description: The IP address of this syslog destination. This value must be a unicast IP address.

usdLogSyslogRowStatus.name: usdLogSyslogRowStatus
usdLogSyslogRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table. Only 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported.

usdLogSyslogSeverity.name: usdLogSyslogSeverity
usdLogSyslogSeverity.description: The severity level for this syslog destination. Setting this value to 'off' suppresses log messages from being sent to this syslog destination.

usdLogSyslogFacility.name: usdLogSyslogFacility
usdLogSyslogFacility.description: The facility id attached to messages sent to this syslog destination.

usdLogDestConsoleSeverity.name: usdLogDestConsoleSeverity
usdLogDestConsoleSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the console. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are sent to this destination.

usdLogDestNvFileSeverity.name: usdLogDestNvFileSeverity
usdLogDestNvFileSeverity.description: The minimum severity level of messages sent to the nonvolatile log file. A value of 'off' indicates no log messages are to be sent to this destination.

usdLogCatTable.name: usdLogCatTable
usdLogCatTable.description: A table describing the characteristics of each log category.

usdLogCatEntry.name: usdLogCatEntry
usdLogCatEntry.description: An entry describing the characteristics of a log category.

usdLogCatIndex.name: usdLogCatIndex
usdLogCatIndex.description: An integer index uniquely associated with a log. Index values do not necessarily persist across system reboots. Following reboot, mappings of (reboot-invariant) log category names to log index values is available in the usdLogCatNameTable.

usdLogCatName.name: usdLogCatName
usdLogCatName.description: The name of this log category.

usdLogCatDescr.name: usdLogCatDescr
usdLogCatDescr.description: A description of the functionality for which events are recorded by this log category.

usdLogCatEngineering.name: usdLogCatEngineering
usdLogCatEngineering.description: An indication of whether this log is intended mainly for engineering development and debug purposes.

usdLogCatDiscards.name: usdLogCatDiscards
usdLogCatDiscards.description: The number of messages generated by this log category that were discarded because of resource limitations.

usdLogCatSeverity.name: usdLogCatSeverity
usdLogCatSeverity.description: The severity level for this log category. The value 'off' disables recording of this log category's messages. For other severity level values, only messages at or above this severity level will be logged in usdLogMsgTable.

usdLogCatVerbosity.name: usdLogCatVerbosity
usdLogCatVerbosity.description: The verbosity level for this log category. Supplementary information may be available for certain event types. This object controls whether that additional information, if available for a given event, is recorded.

usdLogCatNameTable.name: usdLogCatNameTable
usdLogCatNameTable.description: A table mapping each log category's name to its index.

usdLogCatNameEntry.name: usdLogCatNameEntry
usdLogCatNameEntry.description: An entry mapping a log category's name to its index.

usdLogCatNameName.name: usdLogCatNameName
usdLogCatNameName.description: The name of the log category.

usdLogCatNameIndex.name: usdLogCatNameIndex
usdLogCatNameIndex.description: The log index associated with this log category.

usdLogMsgCapacity.name: usdLogMsgCapacity
usdLogMsgCapacity.description: The maximum capacity, in number of log messages, of the usdLogMsgTable.

usdLogMsgLastSeqNumber.name: usdLogMsgLastSeqNumber
usdLogMsgLastSeqNumber.description: The sequence number of the most recent usdLogMsgTable entry. By monitoring this object's rate of change in relation to the usdLogMsgTable capacity, a management client can determine whether it is polling usdLogMsgTable frequently enough to avoid missing log messages.

usdLogMsgTable.name: usdLogMsgTable
usdLogMsgTable.description: A table of log messages generated by this device.

usdLogMsgEntry.name: usdLogMsgEntry
usdLogMsgEntry.description: A log message generated by this device.

usdLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp.name: usdLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp
usdLogMsgSysUpTimeStamp.description: The value of sysUpTime when this log message was recorded.

usdLogMsgSequenceNumber.name: usdLogMsgSequenceNumber
usdLogMsgSequenceNumber.description: A sequence number that uniquely identifies this entry. Sequence numbers are assigned consecutively beginning with 1. More recent entries have higher sequence numbers.

usdLogMsgCatName.name: usdLogMsgCatName
usdLogMsgCatName.description: Name of the log category that contributed this message.

usdLogMsgCatIndex.name: usdLogMsgCatIndex
usdLogMsgCatIndex.description: Index of the log category that contributed this message.

usdLogMsgText.name: usdLogMsgText
usdLogMsgText.description: The text of the log message. Truncation of log message text is indicated by n asterisk character ('*') in the last octet of a maximum-size string.

usdLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp.name: usdLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp
usdLogMsgDateAndTimeStamp.description: The date and time this message was generated.

usdLogMsgThreshold.name: usdLogMsgThreshold
usdLogMsgThreshold.description: Number of log messages which, when added to usdLogMsgTable, cause a usdLogMsgThresholdTrap to be generated. This value is expressed as a percentage of the capacity of usdLogMsgTable. A value of zero disables trap generation.

usdLogMsgThresholdTrap.name: usdLogMsgThresholdTrap
usdLogMsgThresholdTrap.description: This trap is generated to report that an incremental number of log messages (described by the value of usdLogMsgThreshold) have been added to usdLogMsgTable.

usdLogCompliance.name: usdLogCompliance
usdLogCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere Networks, Inc. Log MIB.

usdLogCompliance2.name: usdLogCompliance2
usdLogCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere Networks. Log MIB., including support for multiple SYSLOG destinations.

usdLogGroup.name: usdLogGroup
usdLogGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of Unisphere Networks, Inc. logging capabilities.

usdLogGroup2.name: usdLogGroup2
usdLogGroup2.description: A collection of objects providing management of Unisphere Networks, Inc logging capabilities, including support for multiple SYSLOG destinations.

usdLogTrapGroup.name: usdLogTrapGroup
usdLogTrapGroup.description: A management notification pertaining to logging operations.
